# XJSON Data Definition

XJSON uses ⟁ prefix for keys:

```json
{
  "⟁shard": {
    "⟁id": "users",
    "⟁api": [
      {"⟁path": "/list", "⟁method": "GET"}
    ]
  }
}
```

Use XJSON to define shards, APIs, UIs, and virtual servers.

code.content:
const userShard = {
  id: 'users',
  port: 3001,
  runtime: 'kuhul',
  api: [
    { path: '/list', method: 'GET', handler: 'list_users' }
  ],
  view: {
    html: {
      body: {
        node: 'div',
        children: ['User Management']
      }
    }
  }
};

await klh.registerShard(userShard);

